American National Bank and Trust Company Key Developments

American National Bank and Trust Announces Executive Changes
Apr 3 17
American National Bankshares Inc. announced the retirement of R. Helm Dobbins, Executive Vice President of the Company and its wholly owned subsidiary, American National Bank and Trust Company (Bank), and Chief Credit Officer of the Bank, effective as of March 30, 2017. It was initially reported in the press release dated December 23, 2016 that his retirement date would be March 31, 2017. Edward C. Martin, Executive Vice President of the Bank, has assumed the Chief Credit Officer position.


American National Bank and Trust Company Announces Management Changes, Effective from January 1, 2017
Dec 23 16
American National Bankshares Inc. announced R. Helm Dobbins, Executive Vice President of the company and its wholly owned subsidiary, American National Bank and Trust Company, and Chief Credit Officer of the Bank, will retire on March 31, 2017. At that time, the Chief Credit Officer position will be assumed by Edward C. Martin, who is currently Executive Vice President and Senior Credit Officer of the Bank. Ramsey K. Hamadi, Executive Vice President of the company and the Bank, has been named Chief Administrative Officer of the Bank, effect from January 1, 2017. Martin joined the Bank in September 2016 after serving as chief credit officer of a large Roanoke community bank and as regional credit officer of a multi-state regional bank. Hamadi joined American National in July 2016 and currently leads the Bank's major strategic initiatives from his office in Danville, VA. He has 24 years of financial and accounting experience with 14 of those years as a chief financial officer of regional community banks. American National also announced the promotions, Brandon D. Atkins to Senior Vice President and Senior Risk Officer with his office in Danville, VA. M. Lee Burris to Senior Vice President and Commercial Relationship Manager with his office in Greensboro, NC. William L. Kirby IV to Senior Vice President and Market President, Southside Region with his office in Martinsville, VA by the Bank, effect from January 1, 2017.


American National Bank and Trust Company Appoints John H. Settle, Jr. as EVP and President of Trust and Investment Services
Nov 2 16
American National Bank and Trust Company named John H. Settle, Jr. as EVP and President of Trust and Investment Services. Settle joins the company with over 30 years of experience guiding clients in growing, managing, protecting and transferring wealth. Settle most recently served as senior vice president and senior fiduciary advisor at Wells Fargo, where he and his team helped families and businesses meet their financial goals. Previously, he served as managing director in the Private Wealth Management area of SunTrust.  He currently serves on the Investment Committee of the Cameron Foundation.


